# No em dashes (—)

Do not use the em dash character (`—`, U+2014) anywhere in this project:

- User-facing UI copy (labels, toasts, empty states, chat, onboarding)
- AI system prompts, tool summaries, and model replies
- Commit messages, PR descriptions, and comments you write in-repo
- Docs the product surfaces (README product blurbs, ROADMAP)

## Why

Em dashes are a strong “AI-generated copy” tell. They make the app feel less trustworthy.

## What to use instead

Rewrite so the sentence still reads naturally:

| Instead of | Prefer |
|---|---|
| `Queued — sends when online.` | `Queued. Sends when online.` |
| `Meet Penda — your companion.` | `Meet Penda, your companion.` |
| `Listening — release to send` | `Listening. Release to send` |
| `Status — details follow` | `Status: details follow` |

Prefer a **period** for two clauses, a **comma** for a soft pause, or a **colon** to introduce detail. Spaced hyphen (` - `) is acceptable sparingly; do not replace every em dash with a hyphen mechanically if a period reads better.

## Checklist

Before finishing UI or prompt work, search the touched files for `—` and remove any hits.
